Title: Hopf reductions, fluxes and branes

Authors: Ruben Minasian and Dimitrios Tsimpis

Comments: 22 pages, harvmac; minor corrections, note added; Section 4

corrected; Powers of string coupling fixed, topology of the solution insection 4.1 clarified, to appear in Nucl.Phys.BJournal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B613 (2001) 127-146

We use a series of reductions, T-dualities and liftings to constructconnections between fractional brane solutions in IIA, IIB and M-theory. Wefind a number of phantom branes that are not supported by the geometry, howevermaterialize upon untwisting and/or Hopf-reduction.